NAME: Configure Web Listeners
DESCRIPTION: Configure the three Web Listeners for Application Express to support the Dev, QA, and Prod environments.

NAME: Configure Application Express Instance Administration Settings
DESCRIPTION:
Set the appropriate security and configuration settings for the Application Express development instance using apex_admin.
          Also set instance settings for QA and Prod using the available APIs.

NAME: Assign Workspace Administrators
DESCRIPTION:
In development assign a minimum of two Workspace administators to each workspace.
          These administrators will then be responsible for maintaining developer access within their own workspaces.

NAME: Prepare Course Outline
DESCRIPTION: Creation of the training syllabus

NAME: Write Training Guide
DESCRIPTION: Produce the powerpoint deck (with notes) for the training instructor.

NAME: Develop Training Exercises
DESCRIPTION: Create scripts for sample data and problem statements with solutions.

NAME: Conduct Train-the-Trainer session
DESCRIPTION: Give the training material to the selected developers.

NAME: Train Developers I
DESCRIPTION: Give the training to developers within your group.

NAME: Train Developers II
DESCRIPTION: Give the training to developers within your group.

NAME: Create Oracle Tables
DESCRIPTION: Create table scripts to replicate the SQL Server tables

NAME: Migrate data from SQL Server
DESCRIPTION: Develop scripts to populate the Oracle Tables.

NAME: Convert T-SQL to PL/SQL
DESCRIPTION: Convert the SQL Server database objects across to Oracle Database

NAME: Redevelop Timesheet App
DESCRIPTION: Develop desktop and mobile app for entering timesheets

NAME: Create Shift Schedule App
DESCRIPTION: Create an app for defining when people are scheduled to work different shifts.

NAME: Rengineer Employee App
DESCRIPTION: Create an app for employee details and benefits.

NAME: Customize Customer Tracker Packaged App
DESCRIPTION: Install Customer Tracker from APEX Packaged Apps and use flex fields to meet requirements.

NAME: Migrate data into Customer Tracker tables
DESCRIPTION: Move previous project tracking data into the Customer Tracker EBA_CUST_xxx tables.

NAME: Pilot new Customer Tracker application
DESCRIPTION: Use Customer Tracker to ensure it meets requirements.

NAME: Define scope of Partner Portal App.
DESCRIPTION: Meet with internal and external SMEs and define the requirements

NAME: Design User Experience
DESCRIPTION: Define how partners will interact with the application.

NAME: Develop Admin Screens for Partner Portal
DESCRIPTION: Develop the screens needed to maintain all of the base tables for the Partner Portal app.

NAME: Populate Data Structures for Partner Portal
DESCRIPTION: Upload sample data provided by key partner, and ensure existing tables accessible.

NAME: Design first-cut of main Partner Portal app
DESCRIPTION: Implement the major functional areas and ensure navigation between pages is working correctly.

NAME: Present POC to Key Stakeholders
DESCRIPTION: Walk key stakeholders through the proof of concept and obtain their feedback.

NAME: Define production scope of Partner Portal App.
DESCRIPTION: Define the scope and timelines for the development of the production app.

NAME: Finalize Partner App Data Model
DESCRIPTION: Refine the data model for new and existing entities required to support the Partner Portal.

NAME: Finalize User Experience
DESCRIPTION: Write developer standards on UX and development standards on how partners will interact with the application.

NAME: Refine Admin Screens for Partner Portal
DESCRIPTION: Refine screens developed in the POC to be fully operational to maintain all of the base tables for the Partner Portal app.

NAME: Populate Data Structures for Production Partner Portal
DESCRIPTION: Upload actual data provided by key partner, and ensure existing tables accessible.

NAME: Design production screens for main Partner Portal app
DESCRIPTION: Implement fully functional and complete screens to cover the major functional areasin Phase 1.

NAME: Train Partners
DESCRIPTION: Train selected partners in how to use the Partner Portal app.

NAME: Monitor Partners
DESCRIPTION: Monitor partners selected for the Beta and provide assistance as necessary.

NAME: Review Beta Feedback
DESCRIPTION: Analyse feedback from the partners who participated in the Beta program.

NAME: Improve existing feature functions
DESCRIPTION: Enhance existing features based on responses from Beta partners.

NAME: Add required feature functions
DESCRIPTION: Add missing features outlined in responses from Beta partners.

NAME: Load full production data
DESCRIPTION: Ensure all data required for production roll out are inserted and maintained.

NAME: Test Production Partner Portal
DESCRIPTION: Do full scale testing on the Partner Portal application.

NAME: Install Partner Portall app onto Production Server
DESCRIPTION: Install the database objects and application(s) into the production environment.

NAME: Configure production data load procedures
DESCRIPTION: Install and test data load procedures from internal and external data sources into production environment.

NAME: Provide user credentials for partners
DESCRIPTION: Define user credentials for each partner to allow access to the Partner Portal app.

NAME: Announce Partner Portal app to all partners
DESCRIPTION: Email or call partners to inform them of the new application and instructions on how to get started.
